    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-19T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-19T20:00:00-05:00" n="324"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d324">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.77/247</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the Advisory Commission of Railway Experts to
                        Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SJF1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stevens</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nagasaki</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-20T10:00:00+09:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 20, 1917, 10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 12.16 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For <persName corresp="#p_WD1">Willard</persName>:</p>
                <p>Again strongly advise holding units in Japan. I ought to know shortly if we can
                    go ahead. All units must take some food and bedding on their return to Russia;
                    therefore, both <persName corresp="#p_ECH1">Emerson</persName> and Baldwin must
                    be supplied ample funds. We should all go back <pb facs="0264" n="214"
                        xml:id="pg_214"/> shortly with man-of-war and 5,000 troops. Time is coming
                    to put fear of God into these people. Answer care of Consul of the United
                    States, Yokohama.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stevens</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
